After picking the most reliable method to move through the environment, the threat actor then proceeded to establish beacons across the enterprise. The threat actors requested 600+ bitcoins, which have a market value of around 6+ million USD. During negotiations, using various sources and methods, the threat actors were seen connecting from various countries and cloud service providers. After a few false starts during lateral movement failures, the threat actors performed some additional local system recon. On day 1 the threat actors checked a domain controller for MS17-010 before continuing with more discovery. From there, the threat actor used WMIC to execute the beacon. The threat actor was having issues running beacons on numerous systems, and on at least one of the systems, they mounted the drive remotely. Description: Threat Actor using AdFind for reconnaissance.